Citation.sTitle: Ionic Liquids-Based Aqueous Biphasic Systems with Citrate Biodegradable Salts
Citation.sAbstract: New ionic liquids- aqueous biphasic systems (ABS) containing the imidazolium and pyrrolodinium cation combined with dicyanamide anion and citrate organic salts are investigated. Several ionic liquids (five in total) were evaluated towards their capacity to create aqueous biphasic systems in the presence of two low environmental impact organic salts: potassium and sodium citrate. The capacity of these ILs to form two liquid phases is discussed regarding the alkyl chain length and the cation core of the IL. Besides, the effect of the citrate salt on the phase behaviour has been also addressed. To study the capacity of the ABS, the binodal curves, the tie-lines and respective tie-line lengths were determined at T = 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure, and the tie-lines were correlated using Othmer-Tobias and Bancroft equations. Finally, a comparison between the experimental results obtained here and literature values was carried out. ACS Paragon Plus Environment
